ini_with_includes

Demo for using a #INCLUDE directive(s) in an ini file

Examples:
1) relative file spec (relative to ini dir):
#INCLUDE filename.inc
#INCLUDE ./filename.inc
#INCLUDE ../filename.inc

2) absolute file spec:
#INCLUDE /tmp/filename.inc
#INCLUDE /home/myname/inc/filename.inc

3) tilde file spec:
#INCLUDE ~/machinekit/myincludes/filename.inc

Note:

The .inc suffix is recommended for included files.

Using a .ini suffix would mistakenly allow the partial file to appear as a config choice.
